, what was the question? <span><span class="ref-journal">Am J Bioeth. </span>2002;<span class="ref-vol">2</span>:21\xe2\x80\x9323. doi: 10.1162/152651602320957303.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/12762914" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=529455&amp;issue-id=10201&amp;journal-id=39&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] [<a href="//dx.doi.org/10.1162%2F152651602320957303" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=529455&amp;issue-id=10201&amp;journal-id=39&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CCrosslink%7CDOI">CrossRef</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Am+J+Bioeth&amp;title=Now+that+we+have+the+data,+what+was+the+question?&amp;author=CL+Bosk&amp;volume=2&amp;publication_year=2002&amp;pages=21-23&amp;pmid=12762914&amp;doi=10.1162/152651602320957303&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=529455&amp;issue-id=10201&amp;journal-id=39&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></li><li id="B11"><span class="citation">Chaitin E. Earl Weaver was right: It\'s what you learn after you think you know it all that counts. <span><span class="ref-journal">Am J Bioeth. </span>2002;<span class="ref-vol">2</span>:w1\xe2\x80\x93w2. doi: 10.1162/152651602320957484.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/12762906" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=529455&amp;issue-id=10201&amp;journal-id=39&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] [<a href="//dx.doi.org/10.1162%2F152651602320957484" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=529455&amp;issue-id=10201&amp;journal-id=39&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CCrosslink%7CDOI">CrossRef</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Am+J+Bioeth&amp;title=Earl+Weaver+was+right:+It\'s+what+you+learn+after+you+think+you+k